      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NOT A WORRY (2) gave away a big start and never came on when resuming last start, finishing sixth and beaten 20 lengths over 1200m at Atherton. Meeting a tougher field but on his best form he is one of the chief contenders. ONOMA (4) resumed over 950m at this track where he showed little early speed but got home nicely to finish fourth, beaten 4.5 lengths. Leading player. CHATEAU VON TESS (7) travelled in a rearwards position then made some inroads and finished 3.5 lengths away in fourth last time out over 950m at this track when first up from a spell. Steps up in distance today. Leading hope. HEEZ DE MAN (1) raced on the speed from the outset last start and finished second, beaten 6 lengths, over 1200m at Atherton. Meeting a tougher field but on his best form he is good enough to take this out.",
